  * Change in pointers managed by GC.
    I recommend to always use these pointers with a HB_ITEM, to avoid that
    the GC releases them.
    The counter of references does not avoid that the pointer is freed when the GC
    is executed.
    Only hb_itemPutPtrGC() or hb_gcLock() can preserve the leader correctly.
    I recommend not to use gcLock.
    Changes:
     - garbage.c  - ulHolders start with 0.
     - fastitem.c - hb_itemPutPtrGC() increment reference calling to hb_gcIncRef().
     - fastitem.c - hb_itemClear() decrement reference calling to hb_gcDecRef() and
                    execute hb_gcFree() if not locked with hb_gcLock().
     - inet.c     - use of the pointers protected by a HB_ITEM.
     - thread.c   - delete hb_gcFree() to avoid double elimination.
     - thread.c   - chained of pointers to the structure of thread to be updated when
                    thread finalizes, avoiding errors of access to released memory.
                    This pointers are returned by StartThread() and GetCurrentThread().

